main event: A witness observed a whitish-yellow fireball type object that flew in an unusual, erratic manner near Lansing, Michigan on December 12, 1965.
interesting points: The object was very bright at times and then grew dim and disappeared, but later reappeared.
The object made no sound and moved in an unusual, erratic manner.
The witness observed the object for about 20 minutes after sunset while twilight was still visible.
The witness described the object as resembling an aircraft observation.
The witness had a telescope but could not make out any more details of the object at a distance.
